Task: Implement run_lint() core logic

Summary:
Implemented run_lint(config, path, report_format) in src/gd_tools/lint_runner.py.
The function discovers .gd files via discover_gd_files(), reads each file, and
invokes gdtoolkit.linter.lint_code() to check for issues. All gdlint problems
are treated as errors (gdlint does not distinguish severities — confirmed via
print_problem source which labels all as 'Error'). The warnings list is always
empty since gdlint doesn't produce warnings.

Key API findings:
- gdtoolkit.linter.lint_code(code_string) -> List[Problem]
- Problem has: name, description, line, column (no severity field)
- Syntax errors raise UnexpectedToken (from lark) with .line and .column attrs
- This will be handled in the next task (syntax error handling)

